[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35morg.apache.commons.compress.archivers.examples.Expander.expand[0m[1;39m([0m[39mExpander.jav[0m[1;92ma:400[0m[1;39m)[0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m[1;35mExpanderFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[39mExpanderFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:52[0m[1;39m)[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: a87e9aa6b0374484[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Jazzer fuzzing session against the Apache Commons Compress “Expander” example has[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggered a critical security issue: a file path traversal. During archive [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpansion, the fuzzer invoked `Expander.expand`, which in turn led the Jazzer [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FilePathTraversal` sanitizer to throw a `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` exception, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating that an extracted file path escaped the intended output directory.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue overview  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ExpanderFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m feeds arbitrary data to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.examples.Expander.expand` methods. While[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessing a crafted archive entry, the code constructs a file path that falls [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moutside the designated extraction directory. Jazzer’s `FilePathTraversal.check` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhook detects this and aborts with a critical exception.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  This is a classic file path traversal vulnerability [0m[1;39m([0m[39mCWE-[0m[1;36m22[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Malicious archive [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentries can include sequences like “..[0m[35m/[0m[39m” or absolute paths, causing the extractor [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto write or overwrite files outside its sandbox.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key observations  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The exception stack trace pinpoints the sanitizer’s failure at [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FilePathTraversal.check` → `checkPath` → `pathFirstArgHook`.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The vulnerable code resides in multiple overloads of `Expander.expand` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnotably[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat lines [0m[1;36m86[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m204[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m324[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m400[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m460[0m[39m in the example[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The harness merely calls `expand` with fuzzed input; it is not itself flawed [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbut surfaces the underlying traversal defect.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The temporary directory path shown [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/tmp/expander-tmp.../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdemonstrates that sanitized output paths can be manipulated to escape the target [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mroot.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Areas for further investigation  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. **Expander.expand logic** – all overloads in [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.examples.Expander`; focus on how entry names[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare joined to the output directory.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. **Path normalization and validation** – verify whether `Expander` performs any[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcanonicalization or avoids “..” segments before file creation.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. **Integration with sanitizers** – examine how the fuzzer’s `FilePathTraversal`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhook is wired to the file extraction calls in `Expander`.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. **Archive entry handling** – review code that reads entry metadata [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnames, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattributes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and turns them into local filesystem paths.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInvestigating these components will provide a comprehensive view of how untrusted [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marchive data is handled and where path bounds checks are missing or insufficient.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== Java Exception: com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFile path traversal: [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/expander-tmp9888693390645782134/output/q/r/[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.code_intelligence.jazzer.sanitizers.FilePathTraversal.check[0m[1;39m([0m[39mFilePathTraversal.j[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35morg.apache.commons.compress.archivers.examples.Expander.expand[0m[1;39m([0m[39mExpander.jav[0m[1;92ma:460[0m[1;39m)[0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35morg.apache.commons.compress.archivers.examples.Expander.expand[0m[1;39m([0m[39mExpander.jav[0m[1;92ma:400[0m[1;39m)[0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m472[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m473[0m[39m:    private boolean [0m[1;35mprefersSeekableByteChannel[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal String format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m474[0m[39m:        return [0m[1;35mArchiveStreamFactory.TAR.equalsIgnoreCase[0m[1;39m([0m[39mformat[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mArchiveStreamFactory.ZIP.equalsIgnoreCase[0m[1;39m([0m[39mformat[0m[1;39m)[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m475[0m[39m:                || [0m[1;35mArchiveStreamFactory.SEVEN_Z.equalsIgnoreCase[0m[1;39m([0m[39mformat[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m476[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m477[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m478[0m[39m:    private Path [0m[1;35mtoPath[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal File targetDirectory[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m479[0m[39m:        return targetDirectory != null ? [0m[1;35mtargetDirectory.toPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m : null;[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m480[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m481[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m482[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m52[0m[39m:import org.apache.commons.compress.utils.IOUtils;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m53[0m[39m:import org.apache.commons.compress.utils.ParsingUtils;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m54[0m[39m:import org.apache.commons.compress.utils.TimeUtils;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m55[0m[39m:import org.apache.commons.io.file.attribute.FileTimes;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m56[0m[39m:import org.apache.commons.lang3.SystemProperties;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m57[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m58[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m59[0m[39m: * An entry in a <a [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [33mhref[0m[39m=[0m[32m"https[0m[32m://www.gnu.org/software/tar/manual/html_node/Standard.html"[0m[39m>Tar [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marchive<[0m[35m/[0m[95ma[0m[39m>.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m60[0m[39m: * It consists of the entry's header, as well as the entry's File. Entries can [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe instantiated in one of three[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m61[0m[39m: * ways, depending on how they are to be used.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m62[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m63[0m[39m: * TarEntries that are created from the header bytes read from an archive are [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstantiated with the [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link TarArchiveEntry#[0m[1;35mTarArchiveEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m constructor.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m64[0m[39m: * These entries will be used when extracting from or listing the contents of an[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marchive. These entries have their header filled in using the header bytes. They[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m65[0m[39m: * also set the File to null, since they reference an archive entry not a file.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m66[0m[39m: * <[0m[35m/[0m[95mp[0m[39m>[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m67[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m68[0m[39m: * TarEntries that are created from Files that are to be written into an archive[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare instantiated with the [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link TarArchiveEntry#[0m[1;35mTarArchiveEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[39mFile[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m or[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m69[0m[39m: * [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link TarArchiveEntry#[0m[1;35mTarArchiveEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m constructor. These entries have[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtheir header filled in using the File's information. They also keep a reference[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m70[0m[39m: * to the File for convenience when writing entries.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m71[0m[39m: * <[0m[35m/[0m[95mp[0m[39m>[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m72[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m73[0m[39m: * Finally, TarEntries can be constructed from nothing but a name. This allows [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe programmer to construct the entry by hand, for instance when only an[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m74[0m[39m: * InputStream is available for writing to the archive, and the header [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minformation is constructed from other information. In this case the header fields [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare set[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m75[0m[39m: * to defaults and the File is set to null.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m76[0m[39m: * <[0m[35m/[0m[95mp[0m[39m>[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m77[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m78[0m[39m: * The C structure for a Tar Entry's header is:[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m79[0m[39m: * <[0m[35m/[0m[95mp[0m[39m>[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m80[0m[39m: * <pre>[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m81[0m[39m: * struct header [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m82[0m[39m: *   char name[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m100[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;     [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m TarConstants.NAMELEN    - offset   [0m[1;36m0[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m83[0m[39m: *   char mode[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;       [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m TarConstants.MODELEN    - offset [0m[1;36m100[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m84[0m[39m: *   char uid[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m TarConstants.UIDLEN     - offset [0m[1;36m108[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m85[0m[39m: *   char gid[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m TarConstants.GIDLEN     - offset [0m[1;36m116[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m86[0m[39m: *   char size[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m TarConstants.SIZELEN    - offset [0m[1;36m124[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m87[0m[39m: *   char mtime[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;     [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m TarConstants.MODTIMELEN - offset [0m[1;36m136[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m88[0m[39m: *   char chksum[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;     [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m TarConstants.CHKSUMLEN  - offset [0m[1;36m148[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m89[0m[39m: *   char linkflag[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;   [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m                         - offset [0m[1;36m156[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m90[0m[39m: *   char linkname[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m100[0m[1;39m][0m[39m; [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m TarConstants.NAMELEN    - offset [0m[1;36m157[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m91[0m[39m: *   [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m The following fields are only present in new-style POSIX tar archives:[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m92[0m[39m: *   char magic[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m6[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m TarConstants.MAGICLEN   - offset [0m[1;36m257[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m93[0m[39m: *   char version[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m TarConstants.VERSIONLEN - offset [0m[1;36m263[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m94[0m[39m: *   char uname[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;     [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m TarConstants.UNAMELEN   - offset [0m[1;36m265[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m95[0m[39m: *   char gname[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;     [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m TarConstants.GNAMELEN   - offset [0m[1;36m297[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m96[0m[39m: *   char devmajor[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;   [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m TarConstants.DEVLEN     - offset [0m[1;36m329[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m97[0m[39m: *   char devminor[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;   [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m TarConstants.DEVLEN     - offset [0m[1;36m337[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m98[0m[39m: *   char prefix[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m155[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;   [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m TarConstants.PREFIXLEN  - offset [0m[1;36m345[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m99[0m[39m: *   [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Used if [0m[32m"name"[0m[39m field is not long enough to hold the path[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m100[0m[39m: *   char pad[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;       [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m NULs                    - offset [0m[1;36m500[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m101[0m[39m: * [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m header;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m102[0m[39m: * <[0m[35m/[0m[95mpre[0m[39m>[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m103[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m104[0m[39m: * All unused bytes are set to null. New-style GNU tar files are slightly [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdifferent from the above. For values of size larger than 077777777777L [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m11[0m[39m 7s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or [0m  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand the rest of the field is the binary representation of the number. See[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m106[0m[39m: * [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link TarUtils#[0m[1;35mparseOctalOrBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, int, int[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m107[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m136[0m[39m:        [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocal[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m175[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal ZipException ex[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m176[0m[39m:                final UnrecognizedExtraField u = new [0m[1;35mUnrecognizedExtraField[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ len[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m185[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m186[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m187[0m[39m:        private final ExtraFieldUtils.UnparseableExtraField onUnparseableData;[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m188[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m189[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mExtraFieldParsingMode[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal ExtraFieldUtils.UnparseableExtraField [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monUnparseableData[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m190[0m[39m:            this.onUnparseableData = onUnparseableData;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m191[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m192[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m193[0m[39m:        @Override[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m194[0m[39m:        public ZipExtraField [0m[1;35mcreateExtraField[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal ZipShort headerId[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m195[0m[39m:            return [0m[1;35mExtraFieldUtils.createExtraField[0m[1;39m([0m[39mheaderId[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m196[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m197[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m198[0m[39m:        @Override[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m199[0m[39m:        public ZipExtraField [0m[1;35mfill[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal ZipExtraField field, final byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m data,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfinal int off, final int len, final boolean local[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws ZipException [0m[1;39m{[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m200[0m[39m:            return [0m[1;35mExtraFieldUtils.fillExtraField[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfield, data, off, len, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocal[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The exception is thrown by Jazzer’s `FilePathTraversal` sanitizer at the very [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfirst file‐write in `Expander.expand`, indicating that one of the archive‐entry [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnames yields a path outside the intended extraction directory.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All of the safe, Path‐based overloads in `Expander` delegate to the private [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgeneric method  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        `private <T extends ArchiveEntry> void [0m[1;35mexpand[0m[1;39m([0m[39mArchiveEntrySupplier<T> [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msupplier, ArchiveEntryBiConsumer<T> writer, Path targetDirectory[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     which correctly calls `[0m[1;35mnextEntry.resolveIn[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtargetDirPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39musing the default [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ArchiveEntry.resolveIn`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to normalize and block “zip‐slip” traversals.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - However, the overload that takes an `ArchiveInputStream<?>` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mused by [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mexpand[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString format, InputStream archive, Path targetDirectory, [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCloseableConsumer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m does **not** delegate to this generic, Path‐safe variant; [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstead it is implemented using raw `File` or unbounded Path concatenation based on[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mentry.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which bypasses the built-in `resolveIn` checks.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Fix Approach  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. **Eliminate the unsafe, `ArchiveInputStream`‐centric extraction routine** and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munify it under the generic, `resolveIn`‐backed method.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. In practice:  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Locate the private method [0m[1;39m([0m[39msomewhere near lines [0m[1;36m93[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m150[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with signature  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```java[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         private void [0m[1;35mexpand[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal ArchiveInputStream<?> in, final Path [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtargetDirectory[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         or the equivalent `[0m[1;35mexpand[0m[1;39m([0m[39mArchiveInputStream, File[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method that performs [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`new [0m[1;35mFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtargetDirectory.toFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mentry.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and manual IO.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. **Delete or deprecate** that routine.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Change the callers of that routine—specifically in  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```java[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         public void [0m[1;35mexpand[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal String format,[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                            final InputStream archive,[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                            final Path targetDirectory,[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                            final CloseableConsumer closeableConsumer[0m[1;39m)[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         throws IOException, ArchiveException [0m[1;39m{[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            try [0m[1;39m([0m[39mCloseableConsumerAdapter c = new [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mCloseableConsumerAdapter[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcloseableConsumer[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                final ArchiveInputStream<?> archiveInputStream =[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                    [0m[1;35mArchiveStreamFactory.DEFAULT.createArchiveInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39mformat, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marchive[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[1;35mexpand[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mc.track[0m[1;39m([0m[39marchiveInputStream[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, targetDirectory[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         so that it no longer calls the old `[0m[1;35mexpand[0m[1;39m([0m[39mArchiveInputStream, Path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` but [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstead invokes the generic [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m-arg expansion:  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```java[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mexpand[0m[1;39m([0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m -> [0m[1;39m([0m[39mT[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35marchiveInputStream.getNextEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry, out[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m -> [0m[1;35mIOUtils.copyLarge[0m[1;39m([0m[39marchiveInputStream, out[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           targetDirectory[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor equivalently, use `[0m[1;35mCloseableConsumerAdapter.track[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to wrap both [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msupplier and writer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. **Implement all path resolution through `[0m[1;35mArchiveEntry.resolveIn[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`**  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In the new code path, for every `ArchiveEntry entry`:  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Call `Path output = [0m[1;35mentry.resolveIn[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtargetDirPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. If `[0m[1;35mentry.isDirectory[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, call `[0m[1;35mFiles.createDirectories[0m[1;39m([0m[39moutput[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Else, call `[0m[1;35mFiles.createDirectories[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35moutput.getParent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` then  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           `try [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOutputStream os = [0m[1;35mFiles.newOutputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39moutput[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[39m* copy data *[0m[35m/[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m[39m`  [0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - This guarantees that any “..[0m[35m/[0m[39m” or absolute‐path names are normalized and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrejected before any file I/O.  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Logic  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All the public `[0m[1;35mexpand[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` overloads [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfor `File` or `Path`, `SevenZFile`, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TarFile`, `ZipFile`, `SeekableByteChannel`, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m already funnel into either the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgeneric `[0m[1;35mexpand[0m[1;39m([0m[39mArchiveEntrySupplier, ArchiveEntryBiConsumer, Path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or to the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mArchiveInputStream overload. By removing the unsafe ArchiveInputStream path and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mredirecting it to the generic, we do not alter the API surface or its [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msemantics—archives still expand entry by entry—but now always with the safety [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing directory‐creation and entry‐writing logic remains identical, except [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor the additional boundary check in `resolveIn`, which only rejects potentially [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdangerous entries.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Side‐Effects & Mitigation  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Archives containing legitimate entries with “..” or absolute paths will now [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcause an `IOException` at expansion time. This is desired behavior: such archives [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare malicious or malformed.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any code relying on forgiving handling of odd entry names may need to catch [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe new `[0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Zip slip ..."[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and continue or skip that entry. If broad [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompatibility is required, document the change in release notes.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No harness or fuzzing logic is modified; the same fuzz inputs that previously [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggered a sanitizer violation will now trigger a clean `IOException`, which the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzer will surface as a non‐security failure [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno crash[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Similar Patterns in Codebase  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The private generic method in `Expander` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m67[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m93[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m already demonstrates [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe correct pattern: Path resolution via `[0m[1;35mnextEntry.resolveIn[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtargetDirPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`startsWith` check, and then `[0m[1;35mFiles.newOutputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtargetPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We simply apply that pattern uniformly to the missing ArchiveInputStream [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpansion, removing the manual File‐based variant.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Steps to Implement  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Remove or comment out the `[0m[1;35mexpand[0m[1;39m([0m[39mArchiveInputStream, Path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand its `File` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverload[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m definitions.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. In the `[0m[1;35mexpand[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString format, InputStream archive, Path targetDirectory, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCloseableConsumer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method, replace the call to the removed routine with a call to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe generic overload:  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mexpand[0m[1;39m([0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m -> [0m[1;39m([0m[39mT[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35marchiveInputStream.getNextEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry, out[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m -> [0m[1;35mIOUtils.copyLarge[0m[1;39m([0m[39marchiveInputStream, out[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        targetDirectory[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Add any necessary suppress‐unchecked casts with brief comments, since [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mArchiveInputStream.getNextEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returns a raw `ArchiveEntry`.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. Run the existing test suite [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnone of the example’s tests or external [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregression tests should fail[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   e. Verify with a small TAR/ZIP containing “..[0m[35m/[0m[95mevil.txt[0m[39m” that `[0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Zip [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mslip ..."[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is thrown rather than creating a file.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   f. Validate that the fuzzer no longer reports a `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical`, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbut instead logs only an I/O exception.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   g. Document in CHANGELOG that Expander now enforces strict path‐sanitization on [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mall archive types.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   h. Release patch.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Jazzer fuzzing run against the Apache Commons Compress example “Expander” [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muncovered a critical file path traversal issue. The initial crash log shows [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: File path traversal` being raised when expanding a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrafted archive entry with a malicious path. An attempted patch refactored the call[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto `[0m[1;35mexpand[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`—switching from directly passing the tracked `ArchiveInputStream` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto passing lambda suppliers for entries and copy operations. Despite that change, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe fuzzer still triggers the same path traversal exception in `Expander.expand`.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer reported a [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: File path traversal`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexception.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Stack trace highlights calls in `FilePathTraversal.check` and `pathFirstArgHook`,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvoked from `org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.examples.Expander.expand`.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The vulnerable code path arises during archive entry extraction: an entry with a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrafted file name escapes the intended target directory, triggering the sanitizer.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey Observations  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The exception is consistently raised before any user code in the harness, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating the vulnerability lies in the example expander logic.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Multiple overloaded `expand` methods in `Expander` delegate to one another [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m~[0m[1;36m86[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m204[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m324[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m400[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m460[0m[39m in `Expander.java`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, all eventually calling [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfile-path-sensitive operations.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The sanitizer detects the first argument to file-system methods as a potentially [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmalicious path.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch edited `Expander.java` around line [0m[1;36m304[0m[39m. Original code:[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;35mexpand[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mc.track[0m[1;39m([0m[39marchiveInputStream[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, targetDirectory[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Patched code:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;35mc.track[0m[1;39m([0m[39marchiveInputStream[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;35mexpand[0m[1;39m([0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m -> [0m[1;35marchiveInputStream.getNextEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry, out[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m -> [0m[1;35mIOUtils.copyLarge[0m[1;39m([0m[39marchiveInputStream, out[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      targetDirectory[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In effect, the patch replaces a single-stream-driven expand call with an expand [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverload that takes:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. A supplier for the next entry.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. A bi-consumer for copying entry data.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. The same `targetDirectory`.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Applying the patch did not prevent the sanitizer from flagging a path traversal. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The updated stack trace still points to `Expander.expand` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnow at line [0m[1;36m465[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m as [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe origin of the `FilePathTraversal.check` invocation.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The traversal exception remains reproducible with the same kind of fuzzed input.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The core `Expander.expand` implementation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mall overloads, especially around lines[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m86[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m204[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m324[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m400[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m460[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to understand how entry names are normalized and written to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdisk.  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The path resolution and directory traversal checks around file creation—ensure [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat each extracted path is validated against the `targetDirectory`.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Interaction between the `CloseableConsumerAdapter` tracking and the expand logic [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto confirm no bypass in path-check hooks.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe codebase exhibited a path traversal vulnerability during archive expansion. A [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJazzer fuzzing run triggered a `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` exception from the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FilePathTraversal` sanitizer when `Expander.expand` attempted to write an entry [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith a malicious path. A patch was applied to wrap calls to [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mnextEntry.resolveIn[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtargetDirPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in a try/catch block—skipping entries that [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrow `IOException`—and the archive-expansion invocation was refactored to use [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexplicit supplier/consumer lambdas. Despite these changes, repeated fuzzing still [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproduces the same `FilePathTraversal` exception in `Expander.expand`, indicating [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe traversal issue remains unmitigated.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A Jazzer run reported a critical file path traversal finding:  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: File path [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtraversal: [0m[35m/tmp/expander-tmp9888693390645782134/output/q/r/[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m`  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stack trace pinpoints `Expander.expand` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m86[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m as the point where a [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msanitized path outside the target directory is used.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer entrypoint is [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mExpanderFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[39mExpanderFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:52[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, driving the example [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marchive expander.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key observations in the initial issue  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The call to `[0m[1;35mnextEntry.resolveIn[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtargetDirPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` allowed path traversal [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msequences to persist.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `FilePathTraversal` sanitizer hooks into file-API calls [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., creating [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectories, writing files[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and aborts on suspicious target paths.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Multiple overloads of `expand` propagate the unsafe path into file-system [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moperations without explicit checks beyond normalization.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch attempt details  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `Expander.java` around line [0m[1;36m70[0m[39m:  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Replaced  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `final Path targetPath = nullTarget ? null : [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mnextEntry.resolveIn[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtargetDirPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       with a guarded resolve:  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         – If `nullTarget` is true, `targetPath = null`.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         – Otherwise wrap `[0m[1;35mnextEntry.resolveIn[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtargetDirPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in try/catch.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         – On `IOException`, skip the entry by fetching the next and `continue` the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloop.  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Around line [0m[1;36m304[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39marchive-expansion entrypoint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Changed `[0m[1;35mexpand[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mc.track[0m[1;39m([0m[39marchiveInputStream[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, targetDirectory[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       to an explicit supplier/consumer call:  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         – `[0m[1;35mc.track[0m[1;39m([0m[39marchiveInputStream[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         – `[0m[1;35mexpand[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m -> [0m[1;35marchiveInputStream.getNextEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry, out[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m -> [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mIOUtils.copyLarge[0m[1;39m([0m[39marchiveInputStream, out[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, targetDirectory[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Result after applying the patch  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fuzzing still triggers:  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: File path traversal: [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/expander-tmp10784190491513931452/output/q/r/[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m`  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - New stack trace locations [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `Expander.expand` at line [0m[1;36m97[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m476[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m416[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m340[0m[39m, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m215[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m but the underlying sanitizer violation remains the same.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for further investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The implementation of `[0m[1;35mnextEntry.resolveIn[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and how it handles “..” or [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mabsolute paths.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All call sites in the various `expand` overloads where paths are normalized, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecked, or passed to file-system APIs.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The interaction between the supplier/consumer pattern and the sanitizer’s [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`pathFirstArgHook`—whether certain I/O calls bypass the intended skip logic.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The behavior of `nullTarget` paths and directory-creation logic in [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Files.createDirectories` or similar methods.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Downstream code that consumes `ArchiveEntry` names and writes files, to ensure[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mno unchecked paths slip through.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
